==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decompose
<hw>De`com*pose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Decomposed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Decomposing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧composer</ets>. Cf. <er>Discompose</er>.]</ety> <def>To
separate the constituent parts of; to resolve into original elements; to
set free from previously existing forms of chemical combination; to
bring to dissolution; to rot or decay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decompose</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Decompose
<hw>De`com*pose"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become resolved or
returned from existing combinations; to undergo dissolution; to decay;
to rot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decomposed</ent>⟦br⟧
